      definitions
        entry
          definition "To measure with a metering device."
        entry
          definition "To imprint a postage mark with a postage meter."
        entry
          definition "To regulate the flow of or to deliver in regulated amounts (usually of fluids but sometimes of other things such as anticipation or breath)."
      partOfSpeech verb
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "The basic unit of length in the International System of Units (SI: Système International d'Unités), equal to the distance travelled by light in a vacuum in 1/299 792 458 seconds. The metre is equal to 39 47/127 (approximately 39.37) imperial inches."
      partOfSpeech noun
      synonyms (m)
